threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a MIPS-based IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai. The binary attempts to propagate by brute-forcing Telnet/SSH access on other devices using a large, hardcoded list of common credentials (e.g., `root:vizxv`, `admin:admin`, `root:123456`) found in function `sub_40f798`. It also functions as a downloader, capable of fetching and executing secondary payloads using `wget`, `tftp`, and `ftpget`. This is evidenced by command strings like `/bin/busybox wget http://...` and `GET /dlr. HTTP/1.0`, which are characteristic of this malware family. The sample also enumerates running processes via the `/proc` filesystem, likely to terminate competing malware or security services.
